<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 3:17PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Walker,
southwestern Dade and northwestern Chattooga Counties through 345 PM
EDT...
At 317 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Rising Fawn, or 9 miles
west of Lafayette. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Summerville, Trion, Menlo, Center Post, Rising Fawn, Cloudland,
Berryton and James H. Floyd State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
